.TH PI-SMART-CLOCK 1 "June 2026" "pi-smart-clock 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pi-smart-clock \- Roman numeral smart clock for Linux desktops
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pi-smart-clock
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pi-smart-clock
runs a full-screen SDL2 clock with weather panels, alarms, and optional
NWS-style alert overlays. The application reads configuration from the XDG
Base Directory (usually \fI~/.config/pi-smart-clock/\fR). Example
configuration files are installed under
\fI/usr/share/pi-smart-clock/config/\fR.
.SH CONTROLS
.TP
.B Esc
Quit the application.
.TP
.B M
Open the menu.
.TP
.B Arrow keys
Emulate the rotary encoder.
.TP
.B Space
Emulate the push button.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/pi-smart-clock/
User configuration files.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/pi-smart-clock/
Persistent data (alarms, alert photos).
.TP
.I /usr/share/pi-smart-clock/
Installed application data and configuration examples.
.SH DEPENDS
Requires \fBffmpeg\fR for alarm video playback and DejaVu fonts for the UI.
.SH AUTHOR
Pi Smart Clock contributors.